		    <div class="content page no-sidebar eldt-class-b-theory-course">
        <div class="page-content-wrapper">
                <div class="page-heading">
                    <h1>Class B ELDT Theory Training Online Course</h1>
                </div>
                    <div class="page-body">
                                    <div class="content-block html-text-styles default content-block-one" id="content-block-one">
                                            <div class="content-block-text">
                                                <div class="block outer what-wrapper w-100 hb ha">
    <div class="block inner what w-100 hb ha">
        <div class="block text-content hb ha">
            <div class="block heading hb ha">
                <h2>Understanding Class B Theory Training</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="block info hb ha">
                <p>All drivers, as of Feb 7th, 2022, seeking a Class B CDL for the first time must meet entry-level driver training (ELDT) requirements. This means these individuals must complete an FMCSA-approved Class B theory training course and exam before CDL skills training and testing. This step is now mandatory to obtain your Class B CDL.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="block img-content hb ha">
            <div class="block img hb ha"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="block outer price-wrapper w-100 hb ha">
    <div class="block inner price w-100 hb ha">
